description: {"blocks":[{"key":"eimfi","text":"This protocol is for generating a single cell suspension suitable for isolation of intestine-specific cells through Fluorescence Activated Cell Sorting (FACS) from embryo stage C. elegans. Embryos are mechanically homogenized with 21G syringe needle.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":177,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"84fvv","text":"Centrifuge embryo suspension at 2000 rcf for 1 minute in swinging bucket centrifuge","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"hbn4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ao5ki","text":"Transfer 10 ul of embryo pellet to 1ml of Qiazol and store at -80°C for downstream RNA analysis","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"53r8j","text":"Resuspend the embryo pellet from Step 7 in 0.5 ml egg buffer and 1 ml chitinase (1 U/ml)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"78js5","text":"Incubate for 20 min rotating/nutating at room temperature","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"200qt","text":"Resuspend the embryo pellet in 1 ml of M9 and transfer to a 1.5 ml tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a9tjo","text":"Pellet the embryos at 2000 rcf for 1 minute in a centrifuge","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a4f9p","text":"Pellet the embryos at 200 rcf for 5 min in fixed angle rotor centrifuge","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3kilh","text":"Aspirate and discard the supernatant","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"eb93c","text":"Attach a 21 guage 1¼ inch needle to a sterile 1 ml syringe","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5745q","text":"Quench the pronase treatment by adding 800 ul of L15-10 media to worm slurry","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"10aut","text":"Wash away excess pronase from the worm slurry","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6kdr3","text":"Aspirate and discard the supernatant","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5dp2c","text":"Pellet the worm slurry at 500 rcf for 5 mins in swinging bucket centrifuge cooled to 4ºC","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"4rbg","text":"Aspirate and discard the supernatant","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"777cm","text":" Aspirate 1 ml of the cell-containing supernatant. Keep the pipette away from the pelleted worm debris.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8up29","text":"Dispense the cell suspension though a 35-micron nylon mesh filter into a 5 ml flow cytometry tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7r4db","text":"Perform an additional round of cell harvest for the sorting strain only (Step 21)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1trc4","text":"Total cell suspension volumes:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"cb349","text":"- Control strain = 1ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3994f","text":"- Sorting strain = 2ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5ssjn","text":"- Transfer 70 ul of cells to 1 ml of Qiazol and store at -80°C for downstream RNA analysis","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8oqsr","text":"- Continue to step 24","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"23cfe","text":"- Retain the remaining ~2ml of cells for FACS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":41,"length":4}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"6DB8FAD73B8411EDB7F00A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.protocols.io/view/facs-isolation-of-intestine-specific-c-elegans-cel-b36zqrf6"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3ave8","text":"Resuspend the chitinase treated embryo pellet in 200 ul pronase (15 mg/ml) and 500 ul egg buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3i0j8","text":"Disrupt the embryo vitelline membrane and release cells by passing the embryo suspension through the needle 100 times, generating a worm slurry","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eaq6o","text":"Visually confirm embryo dissociation by viewing a 2 ul sample of worm slurry on a fluorescent microscope","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
